<TITLE> Four die in head-on collision </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Faridpur, June 6 (bdnews24.com)  Four people died in a head-on collision between a bus and a truck at Maskandi in Faridpur district. The accident took place at Dhaka-Khulna highway on Sunday morning at around 5am. The truck's unidentified helper died on the spot. Three others critically injured in the accident died at Faridpur Medical Hospital. None have yet been identified. 12 persons were injured in the collission. The 'AK Travels' bus was heading to Shatkhira from Dhaka and the wood-loaded truck was heading to Dhaka from Khulna. Highway OC Abdur Razzak told bdnews24.com that no case had yet been filed. bdn
